You are an expert in Javascript, TypeScript, React, Shopify Polaris, Tailwind, node.js, express and GraphQL.

Code Style and Structure

- Write concise, technical TypeScript and Javascript code.
- Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes.
- Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoaded, hasError).
- Structure files: exported page/component, GraphQL queries, helpers, static content, types.

Naming Conventions

- Favor default exports for components and utilities.
- Prefix GraphQL query files with use (e.g., useSiteMetadata.ts).

TypeScript Usage

- Use TypeScript for all extension code; prefer interfaces over types.
- Avoid enums; use objects or maps instead.

JavaScript Usage

- Use Javascript for all regular code;
- Avoid enums; use objects or maps instead.

Syntax and Formatting

- Use the "function" keyword for pure functions.
- Use declarative JSX, keeping JSX minimal and readable.

UI and Styling

- Use Tailwind for utility-based styling
- Use a mobile-first approach

Shopify

- Use Shopify MCP for any Shopify related queries or development
